Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 21:41:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat(sync):=20writeback=20rename=20+=20shoe=20a?=
 =?UTF-8?q?uto-assign=20+=20completion=20=E2=9C=93=20pins?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the run-completion loop that was missing: after a Strava
sync, the matched activity now gets renamed to the planned title
("Easy · Apr 14"), the user's preferred shoe for the run-type is
stamped on the activity row, and the planned workout shows a green
✓ DONE pin on the overview hero + an actuals strip on /workout/[date].

· lib/plan-match: pure helpers (activity↔workout match ±15% distance,
  60% completion threshold, shoe-RunType mapper) — single source of
  truth consumed by sync route + UI.
· lib/strava-writeback: PUT /activities/{id} with idempotent prefix
  check, "Easy · Apr 14" title generator with subLabel support.
· /api/strava/sync: new runPlanMatchPass — iterates buildPlanMatches,
  pushes rename + auto-assigns preferred shoe (skips when user has
  manually set shoe_id).
· /api/strava/connect: OAuth scope upgraded to include activity:write.
· /api/overview + /overview: surfaces todayCompletion through the
  data layer; TodayCard hero swaps the SCHEDULED pin for ✓ DONE +
  actual mi when ≥60% planned; greet tile TODAY tile flips to good.
· /workout/[date]: pulls cached activities, surfaces ✓ COMPLETED chip
  + Actuals from Strava tile (mi · duration · pace · HR).
· lib/db: tracking columns writeback_at, writeback_name,
  shoe_auto_assigned_at on strava_activities (idempotent ALTERs).
· tests: 28 cases covering match tolerance, rest-day exclusion,
  completion threshold, title generator, name-already-matches.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
